defs.name: PointSymbol
defs.docs: Sets the symbol used for points. The valid characters are as follows:

defs.name: PointSize
defs.docs: Sets the size of the points. The size acts as a multiplier, with 1.0 being the default.

defs.name: Caption
defs.docs: Sets the caption of the plot element. Set to empty to hide it from the legend.

defs.name: LineWidth
defs.docs: Sets the width of lines.

defs.name: Color
defs.docs:
Sets the color of the plot element. The passed string can be a color name
 (e.g. "black" works), or an HTML color specifier (e.g. "#FFFFFF" is white). This specifies the fill color of a filled plot.

defs.name: BorderColor
defs.docs:
Sets the color of the border of a filled plot (if it has one). The passed string can be a color name
 (e.g. "black" works), or an HTML color specifier (e.g. "#FFFFFF" is white).

defs.name: LineStyle
defs.docs: Sets the style of the line. Note that not all gnuplot terminals support dashed lines. See DashType for the available styles.

defs.name: FillAlpha
defs.docs: Sets the transparency of a filled plot. `0.0` - fully transparent, `1.0` - fully opaque

defs.name: FillRegion
defs.docs: Sets the fill region. See FillRegion for the available regions.

defs.name: ArrowType
defs.docs: Sets what an arrowhead looks like

defs.name: ArrowSize
defs.docs: Sets the size of the arrowhead. This is specified in the units of graph (i.e. `1.0` would make the arrow as big as the graph).

defs.name: PlotOption
defs.value: PlotOption::{PointSymbol, PointSize, Caption, LineWidth, Color, BorderColor, LineStyle, FillAlpha, FillRegion, ArrowType, ArrowSize}
defs.docs:
An enumeration of plot options you can supply to plotting commands, governing
 things like line width, color and others

defs.name: FillRegionType
defs.docs: An enumeration of possible fill regions

defs.name: AlignType
defs.docs: An enumeration of possible text and label alignments

defs.name: DashType
defs.value: DashType::{Solid, SmallDot, Dot, Dash, DotDash, DotDotDash}
defs.docs: An enumeration of possible dash styles

defs.name: Open
defs.docs: An arrow head shaped like a 'V'

defs.name: Closed
defs.docs: An arrow head shaped like an outlined triangle

defs.name: Filled
defs.docs: An arrow head shaped like a filled triangle

defs.name: NoArrow
defs.docs: No arrow head

defs.name: ArrowheadType
defs.docs: An enumeration of possible arrow head styles

defs.name: Fix
defs.docs: Fixes the value to a specific value

defs.name: Auto
defs.docs: Lets the value scale automatically

defs.name: AutoOption
defs.docs:
An enumeration of something that can either be fixed (e.g. the maximum of X values),
 or automatically determined

defs.name: TextOffset
defs.docs: Sets the offset of the label in characters

defs.name: Font
defs.docs: Sets the font of the label. The string specifies the font type (e.g. "Arial") and the number specifies the size (the units are terminal dependent, but are often points)

defs.name: TextColor
defs.docs:
Sets the color of the label text. The passed string can be a color name
 (e.g. "black" works), or an HTML color specifier (e.g. "#FFFFFF" is white)

defs.name: Rotate
defs.docs: Rotates the label by a certain number of degrees

defs.name: TextAlign
defs.docs: Sets the horizontal alignment of the label text (default is left alignment). See AlignType.

defs.name: MarkerSymbol
defs.docs: Sets a marker for the label. By default no marker is drawn. The valid characters are as follows:

defs.name: MarkerColor
defs.docs:
Sets the color of the marker. The passed string can be a color name
 (e.g. "black" works), or an HTML color specifier (e.g. "#FFFFFF" is white)

defs.name: MarkerSize
defs.docs: Sets the size of the marker. The size acts as a multiplier, with 1.0 being the default.

defs.name: LabelOption
defs.value: LabelOption::{TextOffset, Font, TextColor, Rotate, TextAlign, MarkerSymbol, MarkerColor, MarkerSize}
defs.docs: An enumeration of label options that control label attributes

defs.name: OnAxis
defs.docs: Specifies whether the ticks are drawn at the borders of the plot, or on the axis

defs.name: Mirror
defs.docs: If the axes are drawn on the border, this specifies whether to draw the ticks on the opposite border as well

defs.name: Inward
defs.docs: If the axes are drawn on the border, this specifies whether to draw the ticks pointing inward or outward

defs.name: MinorScale
defs.docs: Sets the scale of the minor ticks

defs.name: MajorScale
defs.docs: Sets the scale of the major ticks

defs.name: Format
defs.docs: Format of the tick labels, e.g. "%.1f ms" will produces labels with "1 ms, 2 ms" etc.

defs.name: TickOption
defs.value: TickOption::{OnAxis, Mirror, Inward, MinorScale, MajorScale, Format}
defs.docs: An enumeration of axis tick options

defs.name: Major
defs.docs: Major ticks have position and an optional label. The label may have a single C-style format specifier which will be replaced by the location of the tick

defs.name: Minor
defs.docs: Minor ticks only have position

defs.name: Tick
defs.docs: Specifies a type of axis tick

defs.name: BorderLocation2D
defs.docs: Plot border locations

defs.name: Reverse
defs.docs: Puts curve samples to the left of the label

defs.name: Invert
defs.docs: Displays legend entries in opposite order

defs.name: Horizontal
defs.docs: Makes the legend horizontal (default is vertical)

defs.name: Placement
defs.docs:
Specifies the location of the legend. The first argument specifies the horizontal
 placement with respect to its position, and the second argument specifies the vertical placement

defs.name: Title
defs.docs: Title of the legend

defs.name: MaxRows
defs.docs: Specifies the maximum number of rows, when the legend is vertical

defs.name: MaxCols
defs.docs: Specifies the maximum number of columns, when the legend is horizontal

defs.name: LegendOption
defs.value: LegendOption::{Reverse, Invert, Horizontal, Placement, Title, MaxRows, MaxCols}
defs.docs: Legend options

defs.name: Linear
defs.docs: Draw lines between points of equal value

defs.name: Cubic
defs.docs: Draw somewhat smoother curves between points with equal value.

defs.name: Spline
defs.docs:
Draw an even smoother curve, this time approximating the locations of
 points with equal value (clamped to range from 2 to 100).

defs.name: ContourStyle
defs.docs: Specifies how the contours are drawn

defs.name: Gray
defs.docs: Use a gray palette with a specified gamma

defs.name: Formula
defs.docs:
Use a palette with that uses a predefined formula for each color component.
 Each formula is identified by an integer between [-36, 36]. See gnuplot documentation, or use the pre-defined constants.

defs.name: CubeHelix
defs.docs: Use a cube helix palette, with a certain start (in radians), cycles, saturation and gamma.

defs.name: PaletteType
defs.docs: Specifies what sort of palette to use

defs.name: GRAY
defs.docs: A gray palette

defs.name: COLOR
defs.docs: Default Gnuplot palette

defs.name: RAINBOW
defs.docs: Classic rainbow palette with terrible perceptual properties

defs.name: HOT
defs.docs: A black body palette

defs.name: HELIX
defs.docs: A nice default for a cube helix

defs.name: Graph
defs.docs:
Coordinates are done relative to a graph (i.e. an axis set). (0, 0) is the bottom left corner and (1, 1) is the top right corner.
 You'd use this to place labels and other objects so that they remain in the same place relative to the graph no matter what you have plotted.

defs.name: Axis
defs.docs: Coordinates match those on the axes. You'd use this to place labels and other objects relative to regions of interest in the graph (e.g. labeling the peak of a function)

defs.name: Coordinate
defs.docs: Specifies how to interpret the coordinate passed to a plotting command
